---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import site from '../data/site.json';
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy — Teri Towner" description="How the Teri Towner campaign collects and uses your information.">
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h1>Privacy</h1>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section>
    <div class="container-narrow prose">
      <p><em>Last updated: PLACEHOLDER</em></p>

      <p>The Teri Towner campaign respects your privacy. This page explains what we collect and why.</p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Form submissions</strong> (volunteer, lawn sign, contact, newsletter): name, email, address, phone, and anything you choose to share. Stored in Google Forms / Google Sheets accessible only to campaign staff.</li>
        <li><strong>Donation records</strong>: name, address, and amount — as required by the BC <em>Local Elections Campaign Financing Act</em>. These are reported to Elections BC.</li>
        <li><strong>Website analytics</strong>: anonymized visitor data (pages viewed, approximate location, device type) via Google Analytics. No personally identifying data is collected.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we use it</h2>
      <p>Only for the campaign — to respond to you, coordinate volunteer efforts, deliver lawn signs, and send occasional updates if you've subscribed. We do not sell, trade, or share your information with any third parties.</p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>You can request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal information at any time by emailing {site.email || 'the campaign'}.</p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>We use Google Analytics cookies for anonymous traffic analysis. You can disable cookies in your browser at any time.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions? <a href="/contact/">Contact the campaign</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    padding: var(--space-xl) 0 var(--space-md);
    background: var(--color-cream);
  }
</style>
